name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
notes: ***1ST AND 2ND DOSE ONLY MODERNA VACCINATIONS*** !!!!VACUNAS DE SEGUNDA DOSIS ÚNICAMENTE MODERNA!!! Enter fairgrounds through Gate 12 off of Pacific Avenue. Be prepared to show confirmation of your appointment or you may experience a slightly longer wait. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. Ingresar por la puerta 12 en la avenida Pacífico. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. ***THOSE WHO GET THEIR 1ST MODERNA SHOT WILL NEED TO FIND OTHER ARRANGEMENTS TO RECEIVE THEIR SECOND DOSE BY FINDING A CLINIC AT THE WEBSITE PROVIDED. AQUELLOS QUE RECIBAN SU PRIMERA DISPARO MODERNA DEBERÁN ENCONTRAR OTROS ARREGLOS PARA RECIBIR SU 2ª DOSIS ENCONTRANDO UNA CLÍNICA EN EL SITIO WEB PROPORCIONADO.**** https://prepmod.doh.wa.gov/
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
notes:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register regardless of phase. (If 12-17 years old must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Camano Island Fire and Rescue- COVID Vaccination Site
notes: We are offering Pfizer and Johnson & Johnson's clinic. Pfizer is available for any person 12 years or older. Johnson & Johnson is available for anyone 18 years or older. We will be located at the Eastern most portion of Freedom Park located at Terry's Corner. If it is your second dose, you will need to bring proof of your first dose. We cannot vaccinate you without proof.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Westport SBRFA Training Center
notes: This clinic is at the Westport South Beach Region Fire Authority Training center for the Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) COVID-19 vaccine. The Janssen vaccine is approved for everyone 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the nose and mouth. Everyone receiving the COVID-19 vaccine is required to stay 15 to 30 minutes under observation.
